Drama unfolded today at the Mombasa law courts when Malindi member of parliament Aisha Jumwa&rsquo;s lawyers demanded to be paid first before they could hand over files to her new legal team. The lawyers, who claimed they had not been paid for their services, were representing Jumwa in a case involving conspiracy to commit fraud by irregularly paying sh19 million to multi-serve contractors through the Malindi CDF kitty.